Okay, next we come to brown paper packages, and this is very apt with themes to delight

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:48.520
in.

00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:54.440
Okay, so themes to delight in, again, kind of a standard boring slide.

00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:58.359
But we can easily change our themes.

00:10:58.359 --> 00:11:05.159
So I used the super exciting default theme in this presentation, aesthetics are something

00:11:05.159 --> 00:11:07.520
I'm working on as well.

00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:13.840
And so you can see, that's going to work, play, yes, okay.

00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:15.520
But I can change the theme.

00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:21.239
So Cordo has some built-in themes, dark being one of them.

00:11:21.239 --> 00:11:26.799
And so you see, I re-render, the theme changes, I'm ready to go, I'm going to try solarized,

00:11:26.799 --> 00:11:29.479
which I actually really like.

00:11:29.479 --> 00:11:31.320
That's another theme.

00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:33.640
So these are the built-in themes.

00:11:33.640 --> 00:11:38.239
But again, if we refer back to one of the talks yesterday that said, something you really

00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:44.119
can do to help yourself a lot is to build themes for your organization, for yourself,

00:11:44.119 --> 00:11:49.840
that you use time and again, that match whatever it is that you need to be doing for your organization,

00:11:49.840 --> 00:11:53.200
for yourself, meet whatever standards you need.

00:11:53.200 --> 00:11:57.559
And so you could spend a lot of time building your own theme, but I bet already people in

00:11:57.559 --> 00:12:01.000
this room are starting to make amazing themes.

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:05.599
And so the opportunity to share these with each other and easily switch back and forth

00:12:05.599 --> 00:12:10.679
is really meaningful because I'm not spending time recreating my slides every time, I can

00:12:10.679 --> 00:12:14.119
just change the theme and have a different look and feel.

00:12:15.119 --> 00:12:21.280
All right, finally, we're at tied up with string and formats to share.

00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:24.280
So tied up with string is really the end, right?

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:28.479
You have your presentation, you need to share it.

00:12:28.479 --> 00:12:33.559
Mene and Julie did a great job this morning talking about all the different formats that

00:12:33.559 --> 00:12:34.799
you can share in.

00:12:34.799 --> 00:12:38.080
So this here is an HTML presentation.

00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:39.080
That's great.

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:40.080
It works right in my browser.

00:12:41.039 --> 00:12:44.400
I didn't have any issues with that.

00:12:44.400 --> 00:12:48.840
And it also is really good for accessibility because you can make use of all the things

00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:54.200
that are already built into HTML around screen readers, colors.

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:58.760
So people are able to make use of the settings that they have in their browser already when

00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:00.880
you're sharing HTML.

00:13:00.880 --> 00:13:09.080
Lots of times we do need PDFs to share, distribute, print out, and carry around with us.

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:13.320
So PDFs are something that is straightforward from these as well.

00:13:13.320 --> 00:13:17.679
Again, all the same document, creating all of these different formats.

00:13:17.679 --> 00:13:24.200
And finally, I really appreciate the work that the Cordo team has put into making PowerPoints.

00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:28.140
There are a lot of organizations that need to use PowerPoints.

00:13:28.140 --> 00:13:32.799
So if you are in one of those organizations, you are probably not culturally going to be

00:13:32.799 --> 00:13:36.760
able to shift your entire organization over to using Cordo.

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:39.719
One, because culture change is hard.

00:13:39.719 --> 00:13:46.239
But two, there are requirements in government agencies and drug discovery around the kinds

00:13:46.239 --> 00:13:49.119
of information that you share and how you share it.

00:13:49.119 --> 00:13:52.919
So I think what we've talked about a lot in this meeting is meeting people where they

00:13:52.919 --> 00:13:57.960
are, understanding what people need, and building towards that rather than saying, like, oh,

00:13:57.960 --> 00:14:04.280
you need to be doing this or some idea of what's best is really creating opportunities

00:14:04.400 --> 00:14:07.520
for people to do what it is they need to do in their context.

00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:15.640
So PowerPoint is one you would change in that header where we are changing the theme.

00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:19.679
You can at the beginning say that you want a PowerPoint output, and you can make a PowerPoint

00:14:19.679 --> 00:14:21.599
output from within Cordo.

00:14:21.599 --> 00:14:26.200
And again, you have all those advantages of being able to integrate your code and your

00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:32.119
visualization and you're not doing what I did, which would be like, get it out of R,

00:14:32.119 --> 00:14:36.719
put it into Illustrator, then take it from Illustrator and put it into PowerPoint.

00:14:36.719 --> 00:14:40.000
So those days are at least a little bit behind me.

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:46.159
But looking ahead, I'm so excited about the opportunities that this presents.

